  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fostering Shock Response Capacities for Social Protection and Economic Integration, With a Focus on the Rights of the Venezuelan Population and Their Host Communities, in the Disaster Risk-Prone Areas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will focus on strengthening capacities of national entities responsible for providing social protection services and welfare during emergency and disaster response, recuperation, and socioeconomic integration. The activities are developed together at the central government level with the regional governments of Tumbes, Piura, Lambayeque, La Libertad and Lima, and the institutions and communities of Venezuelan and host populations present in the main cities in the targeted regions that are highly prone to disasters. The action promotes State institutions having improved services offered regarding social protection and the socioeconomic integration of the Venezuelan population under dignified living conditions; institutions having strengthened spaces and mechanisms for DRM; and the Venezuelan population and the host communities being better informed and prepared to face emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
